Arch Says Catastrophes to Cost Up to $100 Million in Quarter

-- B y   B r o o k e   S u t h e r l a n d
-- 
2011-06-28T13:26:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/arch-says-catastrophes-to-cost-up-to-100-million-in-quarter.html
Arch Capital Group Ltd. (ACGL) , the
Bermuda-based insurer and reinsurer, said catastrophes will cost
the company $90 million to $110 million in the second quarter.  Most of the disasters occurred after March 31, including
storms in the U.S., the company said today in a statement
distributed by  Business Wire .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brooke Sutherland in New York at 
 Bsutherland5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  